The paper discusses a neural network-based approach for knowledge base-based question answering, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and databases (cs.DB). The use of neural attention and global knowledge information also suggests a focus on deep learning and knowledge representation, which further supports these categories.
